# Docs consistency guard (Cursor)

When editing any file matching the globs above (spec docs, including `docs/idea.md`, or AGENTS.md), you MUST run the
**"Docs consistency check"** defined canonically in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).

Do not restate the steps here — follow the version in AGENTS.md so there is only one copy. In
short: read `docs/index.md` §0 (one fact, one owner), don't restate a fact owned by another doc,
keep every `F-###` traced to a QA test, keep auth declared on every network surface, keep the
Google-tech requirement satisfied via Firebase + Gemini, and never reintroduce "Google Maps" or
"OpenRouteService" as the map/routing stack (it's MapLibre GL + OpenFreeMap for render, a
client-side Rust/WASM routing engine for routing — see `docs/06-system-design.md`).
